text: Haramosh Peak is a mountain in the Karakoram range, in Pakistan. Skil Brum is part of the Rakaposhi-Haramosh subrange. It is the 68th highest mountain in the world. The first people to reach the top were an Austrian expedition, in 1958. == References == Category:Mountains of Gilgit-Baltistan Category:Karakoram
